4 minutes ago, Matchlight said:

Unfortunately no, but it is something I have been trying to get work. I've tracked down a 1.3.0 scatterer Beta release which introduces water refractions yet has a few serious bugs. I want to see if the bugs can be flattened out first, while in the meantime I am implementing the 'reddish colour' and UVnoise.

Thank you very much, I suspected the same with respect to the experimental version of scatterer. I'm pleasantly surprised by the performance your mod offers without implementing terrain textures yet.
Thank you very much for your work.

46 minutes ago, Matchlight said:

Unfortunately no, but it is something I have been trying to get work. I've tracked down a 1.3.0 scatterer Beta release which introduces water refractions yet has a few serious bugs. I want to see if the bugs can be flattened out first, while in the meantime I am implementing the 'reddish colour' and UVnoise.

 

After installing the latest version of Scatterer and EVE (Before 1.3.0) I found that the 'reddish' colour isn't there. So i'm not sure whats going on.

Scatterer does not have a 1.3 beta. That version is for 1.2.2, hence the problems everyone is seeing

Alright, there are still a couple of things I don't understand about how you're packaging the mod.

Firstly, what happened to modularity? Sure, it bloats the download size, but it would be incredibly simple to implement and would be a blessing for those who have weaker computers. No point of having steps if there's minimal modularity.
The Laythe cloud textures are Astronomer's clouds for Jool. Don't take credit on that, all you did was tweak the configuration so that they used the two base cloud layers of Jool. 
Why are you getting people to extract the entire KSPRC folder just for the terrain, including the Atmospheres and CityLights? The cloud config for KSPRC is even present in "Andromeda Visuals". Why not just get people to delete Atmospheres and CityLights rather than adding extra fat to the mod?
You're being incredibly vague when crediting people for their components that make up the mod, forgetting to even credit PlanetShine, TextureReplacer, DistantObjectEnhancement, and scatterer!
Astronomer should be credited for more than just the cloud textures, he originally made all of the cloud configurations present in this mod.

7 hours ago, Galileo said:

Scatterer does not have a 1.3 beta. That version is for 1.2.2, hence the problems everyone is seeing

I suppose so, Although I would think that some of these features would be implemented into Scatterer 1.3

3 hours ago, themaster401 said:

Alright, there are still a couple of things I don't understand about how you're packaging the mod.

Firstly, what happened to modularity? Sure, it bloats the download size, but it would be incredibly simple to implement and would be a blessing for those who have weaker computers. No point of having steps if there's minimal modularity.
The Laythe cloud textures are Astronomer's clouds for Jool. Don't take credit on that, all you did was tweak the configuration so that they used the two base cloud layers of Jool. 
Why are you getting people to extract the entire KSPRC folder just for the terrain, including the Atmospheres and CityLights? The cloud config for KSPRC is even present in "Andromeda Visuals". Why not just get people to delete Atmospheres and CityLights rather than adding extra fat to the mod?
You're being incredibly vague when crediting people for their components that make up the mod, forgetting to even credit PlanetShine, TextureReplacer, DistantObjectEnhancement, and scatterer!
Astronomer should be credited for more than just the cloud textures, he originally made all of the cloud configurations present in this mod. 

I'm trying to make things simple to install. Yes, I could go through with pages of instructions and whatnot but at the end of the day, I am trying to make it simple to install. Yes, there is a point in having steps, so people can understand what's a dependency, what it runs from and extras. I apologise for not crediting those mods, that will be fixed. 

 

My point is people don't want to spend forever reading text files in the mod trying to figure out what goes where! I made it that way from personal experience. I may eventually release a lite version, although from what I'm seeing currently performance is not bad. (Compared to other packs I've used) It's no 'EVE' but performance isn't really an issue.

Also, why every time I make a small incremental change you feel the need to push all the non-perfect things down my throat? I don't do that to you.

Edited May 29, 2017 by Matchlight

I apologize if it feels like that. I guess I should respect that there will be imperfections in some KSP mods, especially those of magnitudes as large as this one. But often these imperfections I point out happen to be with licensing and credit, something that should be taken very seriously, especially as mods that have very touchy licenses are present here. One slip up and the entire thing could be sabotaged.

Other than that, it is rude of me to attempt to enforce my opinions at all. It is your choice what to do with the mod.

Thanks, bare in mind not even at 0.4 yet which I will change many of Astronomer's Textures to my own (I can't make textures so my friend is :) 

Some (Pretty much confirmed) features for 0.4

- Wormhole (It's own thing now)

- New clouds for Eve, Jool and Kerbin

- Refreshed Dust storms

Possible Features

- Geysers for Eeloo and Vall (Possibly similar to that of KSPRC)

- Custom made Skybox (Basically a higher-res version of the current one)

1 hour ago, Matchlight said:

I suppose so, Although I would think that some of these features would be implemented into Scatterer 1.3

Well yes those will be included in 1.3, I was just stating that the experimental was not developed on or for 1.3. I just don't want people to read your comment about a scatterer beta when there isn't one. That would just lead to chaos and bug reports that don't need to happen:)

11 hours ago, Spin said:

Thank you very much, I suspected the same with respect to the experimental version of scatterer. I'm pleasantly surprised by the performance your mod offers without implementing terrain textures yet.
Thank you very much for your work.

Great to here about performance, Mostly because I am using Edge of Oblivion as a base which was a little more optimised than Interstellar, yet many things from Interstellar have been installed. Before 0.4 there will be small incremental updates which will include scatterer changes, UVnoise and updates to Dependencies.
Something I have always wanted is to have "sentient blood mist" on Eve, small very low altitude red clouds that are hard to find and produce an ominous noise.

1 hour ago, RuBisCO said:

Something I have always wanted is to have "sentient blood mist" on Eve, small very low altitude red clouds that are hard to find and produce an ominous noise. 

Interesting... It will be considered. I can make them rare to find and in a polar orbit, they rarely come back to the same place quickly. I'm not sure about adding a noise to them but I do think it might be possible.

Wow this mod looks great.

 

I just wanted to post that I was experiencing crashes after installing your modpack. By process of elimination I narrowed the problem down to BoulderCo and Modularflight. Both folders will cause crash on start-up. 

 

I'm running ksp with everything else so I'm not sure what i'm missing by excluding those two folders. 

 

Thanks for your mod!
